</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kinelaria>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 433<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/02 9:52:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7647.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: agro!</span><hr size=1> I always seem to get more aggro when a damage spell is fully resisted than if it landed for full damage. Granted, this is purely from casual observation, but it has seemed this way to me for years now. I cannot explain it, just seems the way it is.<br>
<br>
I don't mind the aggro from FoT really, it's a powerful spell for us, and does need it's limits.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
Lana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=conjem>Conjem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/02 10:43:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7647.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: agro!</span><hr size=1> 90 percent of the time I get summoned it is from full a resist.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc>Wezloc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/02 10:47:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7647.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: agro!</span><hr size=1> Same here if I get full resist i get summoned or pick up aggro right away. Also Fire Bolt of Tallon is not a full time nuke from what i have seen. This spell really can't be chain nuked and has large aggro which limits it. I find myself using SoFB because I have less risk of aggro, and since mobs are hitting for 400+, getting aggro is bad.  I have also observed that healing and slow aggro has increased in PoP. <br>
<br>
Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balasarius>Balasarius</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Italics</span><br>  Posts: 361<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/02 12:53:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7647.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: agro!</span><hr size=1> FoT has low aggro in my experience.  Soloing in PoN, I need to chain cast it as fast as I can to kill the mob before it kills the pet.  I start nuking when the mob is at 90% and don't let up until it's dead.  Sometimes I get do get aggro, but usually I don't.  Go Epic!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
